### Container implementation

```css
.container {
  width: 100%;
  padding-inline: 20px; /* mobile default */
}

@media (min-width: 768px)  { .container { padding-inline: 32px; } }
@media (min-width: 1024px) { .container { padding-inline: 48px; } }
@media (min-width: 1280px) { .container { padding-inline: 64px; } }
@media (min-width: 1440px) { .container { padding-inline: 80px; } }
@media (min-width: 1920px) { .container { padding-inline: 5vw;  } }
@media (min-width: 2560px) { .container { padding-inline: 8vw;  } }
@media (min-width: 3840px) { .container { padding-inline: 12vw; } }
```

NO max-width on .container. Content is never capped.

### Full-bleed (only these two)

1. **`h1.type-hero`** in the hero canvas strip — headline only; full width of the viewport band with `padding-inline` from the page gutter scale (see `.hero-text` in globals). Subtitle, trust bar, and nav CTAs stay in the normal padded flow.
2. **Closing CTA section** (`.cta`) — entire block edge-to-edge horizontally (background band); inner `.wrap` supplies `padding-inline`. No layout `max-width` cap on wrappers.

```css
/* Example: breakout when nested inside a padded parent (rare on this landing) */
.full-bleed {
  width: 100vw;
  margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
  margin-right: calc(50% - 50vw);
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

### Typography responsive

```css
/* These scale — clamp() — canonical hero min = 72px (not 48px; 48px was draft) */
.type-hero    { font-size: clamp(72px, 12vw, 168px); }
.type-display { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 96px);  }

/* These are fixed — NEVER scale */
.type-heading     { font-size: 48px; }
.type-subheading  { font-size: 32px; }
.type-heading-md  { font-size: 24px; }
.type-body-lg     { font-size: 18px; }
.type-body        { font-size: 16px; } /* MINIMUM — never go below */
.type-body-sm     { font-size: 14px; }
/* All mono types: always fixed */
```

### Grid columns

```css
.grid {
  display: grid;
  gap: 16px; /* mobile gutter */
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .grid {
    gap: 24px;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(8, 1fr);
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .grid {
    gap: 24px;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1280px) {
  .grid { gap: 32px; }
}
```

